1
00:00:16,808 --> 00:00:18,284
They're good.

2
00:00:18,284 --> 00:00:20,787
It's not just them.

3
00:00:20,787 --> 00:00:22,956
They have perfect harmony.

4
00:00:22,956 --> 00:00:25,725
They probably didn't have
time to rehearse together.

5
00:00:25,725 --> 00:00:27,160
How is this possible?

6
00:00:28,895 --> 00:00:32,432
I told you I performed
this music before, right?

7
00:00:32,899 --> 00:00:35,201
So I have the conductor's score memorized.

8
00:00:35,735 --> 00:00:37,270
Will you leave it to me?

9
00:00:43,502 --> 00:00:46,129
A pianist did well
as a conductor, too.

10
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:48,882
Give a cellist a chance, too.

11
00:00:48,882 --> 00:00:51,484
Have I ever disappointed you?

12
00:01:30,164 --> 00:01:32,034
What are you doing here
just before our stage?

13
00:01:32,034 --> 00:01:35,670
What are you doing here,
and not at the rehearsal as the pianist?

14
00:01:37,652 --> 00:01:40,142
This is a great performance!

15
00:01:40,142 --> 00:01:42,602
Of course it's Lee Yoon Hoo!

16
00:01:43,812 --> 00:01:47,348
He knows how to possess people's hearts.

17
00:01:47,823 --> 00:01:52,494
He already has the members
on his side.

18
00:01:55,303 --> 00:01:56,420
That's great.

19
00:01:56,420 --> 00:01:57,701
Of course.

20
00:01:57,701 --> 00:01:59,435
But this is it.

21
00:02:01,747 --> 00:02:05,284
The star of the day... is me.

22
00:02:43,956 --> 00:02:45,683
Weren't we just awesome today?

23
00:02:45,683 --> 00:02:48,126
- This is why we play in an orchestra!
- That's what I mean!

24
00:02:48,126 --> 00:02:51,392
My heart is still pounding.

25
00:02:51,392 --> 00:02:53,164
Me too, Su Min.

26
00:02:56,423 --> 00:02:57,649
Thank you, Lee Yoon Hoo.

27
00:02:57,649 --> 00:02:59,596
Juilliard is different for sure.

28
00:02:59,596 --> 00:03:02,396
How can you lead so well
at your first time?

29
00:03:02,396 --> 00:03:04,852
It was possible because
I was familiar with the music.

30
00:03:04,852 --> 00:03:08,288
And you guys prepared very well.

31
00:03:12,119 --> 00:03:15,456
My friend, where have
you been all this time?

32
00:03:16,037 --> 00:03:18,565
By the way,
where did Seol Nae Il go?

33
00:03:18,565 --> 00:03:21,267
She thought she saw
Yoo Jin, so she ran out...

34
00:03:24,580 --> 00:03:26,915
Seol Nae Il is getting
ahead of herself again.

35
00:03:28,917 --> 00:03:31,252
Cha Yoo Jin wouldn't come here.

36
00:03:38,635 --> 00:03:40,169
Sunbae!

37
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:47,152
Did you see our performance?

38
00:03:47,152 --> 00:03:49,323
How was it?

39
00:03:49,323 --> 00:03:51,940
Everyone worked really hard for it.
With Yoon Hoo...

40
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:54,109
The performance was good.

41
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:59,020
I didn't come to see you though.

42
00:03:59,020 --> 00:04:03,244
You could just say that you
came to see me and let it go.

43
00:04:03,244 --> 00:04:04,801
You're coming to my performance, right?

44
00:04:04,801 --> 00:04:06,762
Of course, definitely

45
00:04:06,762 --> 00:04:09,128
I'm going to get changed and dress up.

46
00:04:09,128 --> 00:04:10,863
Then hurry up.

47
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:14,114
Don't miss anything from
the beginning to the end.

48
00:04:14,114 --> 00:04:16,037
Watch and listen carefully.

49
00:04:17,345 --> 00:04:18,769
What?

50
00:04:23,003 --> 00:04:25,130
I'll be there soon!

51
00:04:25,130 --> 00:04:29,234
I'll keep my eyes wide
open in the very front.

52
00:04:49,039 --> 00:04:53,060
Oh, I like your style.

53
00:04:57,090 --> 00:04:59,424
You look better with your hair down.

54
00:04:59,424 --> 00:05:01,718
Wild and sexy!

55
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:03,753
I'll follow my own style.

56
00:05:04,429 --> 00:05:06,598
Did someone tell you not to?

57
00:05:06,598 --> 00:05:09,000
You look ready already.

58
00:05:09,643 --> 00:05:11,959
Please stop with the odd comments.

59
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:15,435
When you have a range of emotions, your
music will become plentiful as well.

60
00:05:15,435 --> 00:05:17,471
Don't try to hide your emotions.

61
00:05:17,471 --> 00:05:19,798
Showing all the emotions

62
00:05:19,798 --> 00:05:22,334
doesn't mean you'll have
a great performance.

63
00:05:23,350 --> 00:05:27,354
Have you ever shown
your emotions properly?

64
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:32,672
You only tried to express the
music when you conducted.

65
00:05:32,672 --> 00:05:37,444
If you're embarrassed to show your
emotions, you won't develop anymore.

66
00:05:37,945 --> 00:05:42,449
How you will make use
of this performance...

67
00:05:42,449 --> 00:05:45,606
Let me have the fun watching it.

68
00:05:45,606 --> 00:05:47,496
I got it.

69
00:05:47,496 --> 00:05:51,095
I'll give you more than
enough fun to watch me.

70
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:24,376
Piano concerto in A minor by Grieg.

71
00:06:24,376 --> 00:06:29,114
The composer Grieg was
as good in piano as a pianist.

72
00:06:29,744 --> 00:06:33,705
Is that why Cha Yoo Jin
also chose this music?

73
00:06:34,365 --> 00:06:39,880
My apprentice, it's going to be
a fun time in music now.

74
00:07:02,089 --> 00:07:05,327
Have you ever seduced anyone?

75
00:07:06,844 --> 00:07:12,079
'I want to steal someone's glance,
I want to capture her eyes.'

76
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:15,849
'I want to seduce her,
I want to steal her heart.'

77
00:07:16,516 --> 00:07:18,885
You've never had that thought, have you?

78
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:25,054
Well, you probably
already caught their eyes

79
00:07:25,054 --> 00:07:28,390
so you didn't have to seduce anyone.

80
00:07:30,868 --> 00:07:37,457
Performers on stage have to provoke
and attract the audience.

81
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:42,362
You have to have passion with the wish
to steal the ears and eyes of the audience.

82
00:09:55,179 --> 00:09:58,282
Wow, Cha Yoo Jin was really great.

83
00:09:59,939 --> 00:10:03,103
It looks like a real star
is born in our school.

84
00:10:03,103 --> 00:10:05,564
If S Orchestra is dissolved and

85
00:10:05,564 --> 00:10:08,763
von Stresemann goes back to his place

86
00:10:08,763 --> 00:10:11,933
we'll have things organized, right?

87
00:10:19,906 --> 00:10:23,931
A young man like you are that tired?

88
00:10:23,931 --> 00:10:26,032
I poured out everything.

89
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:29,995
Like someone said,
I didn't want to do it half-way.

90
00:10:33,050 --> 00:10:36,453
You should take care of your health now.
Think about your age.

91
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:41,312
Don't be embarrassed of your emotions.
Express them.

92
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:46,734
How dare you try to teach me?

93
00:10:46,734 --> 00:10:48,368
It's painful to watch.

94
00:10:49,609 --> 00:10:52,545
How come your dating life is so boring...

95
00:10:53,140 --> 00:10:56,330
You told me to express
my emotions in a full scale.

96
00:10:56,330 --> 00:10:58,123
That way, when I perform
the next time...

97
00:10:58,123 --> 00:11:04,529
We won't have any occasion
to be together anymore.

98
00:11:05,399 --> 00:11:07,167
Professor...

99
00:11:08,007 --> 00:11:14,046
Two conductors can't stand
on stage together.

100
00:11:23,224 --> 00:11:26,476
Our performances together
are over as of today.

101
00:11:34,862 --> 00:11:37,365
It was a great performance.

102
00:11:39,179 --> 00:11:40,923
Cha Yoo Jin...

103
00:11:41,618 --> 00:11:49,659
I am a little... this tiny bit proud of you.

104
00:11:51,086 --> 00:11:55,840
I am quite a bit proud
of you, Professor.

105
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,398
Cheeky!

106
00:12:00,262 --> 00:12:05,401
That's just like my apprentice.

107
00:12:06,634 --> 00:12:08,268
Cha Yoo Jin!

108
00:12:08,856 --> 00:12:11,191
Reporters are waiting for
you at the photo zone.

109
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:15,435
Of course Professor von Stresemann
won't be coming out, right?

110
00:12:18,697 --> 00:12:21,366
Go out there, my apprentice.

111
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:26,671
It's like a show you
have to do to grow more.

112
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:40,853
This is not just a simple publicity.

113
00:12:46,849 --> 00:12:49,185
You said you don't like
this kind of thing.

114
00:12:49,185 --> 00:12:50,896
What choice do I have?

115
00:12:50,896 --> 00:12:53,431
I should help with marketing Cha Yoo Jin.

116
00:12:54,233 --> 00:12:57,444
Anyway, that man will
probably see this article.

117
00:12:57,444 --> 00:12:59,946
He probably doesn't even know
about your debut as a conductor.

118
00:13:00,954 --> 00:13:02,956
Don't talk about Father.

119
00:13:15,671 --> 00:13:18,440
That's her.
Get a shot with her.

120
00:13:21,426 --> 00:13:23,194
Thanks.

121
00:13:25,347 --> 00:13:31,111
Everyone here are our,
Han Eum's, pride Mr. Cha Yoo Jin

122
00:13:31,111 --> 00:13:34,506
and Miss Han Eum, Chae Do Kyung
voice major.

123
00:13:34,506 --> 00:13:36,942
They are the faces of our school.

124
00:13:36,942 --> 00:13:39,426
Please, take their pictures.

125
00:13:39,426 --> 00:13:41,019
They would make a perfect couple.

126
00:13:41,019 --> 00:13:42,078
Thank you.

127
00:13:42,078 --> 00:13:45,576
Could the three of you stand together?
It will be a good photo.

128
00:13:45,576 --> 00:13:46,944
Ma'am.

129
00:13:47,703 --> 00:13:49,271
Thank you.

130
00:13:50,581 --> 00:13:52,624
Don't they look great as mother and son?

131
00:13:52,624 --> 00:13:54,895
Get a real close-up.

132
00:13:54,895 --> 00:13:57,097
Excuse me, just for a second.

133
00:14:00,534 --> 00:14:04,471
My boss's son is... Yoo Jin?

134
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:28,167
Hurry up!

135
00:14:30,745 --> 00:14:32,413
Don't go there.

136
00:14:32,413 --> 00:14:34,632
You're going to be humiliated.

137
00:14:34,632 --> 00:14:37,749
My boss's son was Yoo Jin...

138
00:14:37,749 --> 00:14:40,702
Chae Do Kyung was such a cunning fox...

139
00:14:40,702 --> 00:14:43,050
Calling her, 'Mother, Mother,' everyday...

140
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:45,820
- Chae Do Kyung?
- Yes.

141
00:14:46,720 --> 00:14:50,156
How long are you going to wear this?
Go change now.

142
00:14:54,228 --> 00:14:56,063
Hi, Il Lak.

143
00:14:56,063 --> 00:14:58,332
I'm with Nae Il now.

144
00:14:59,406 --> 00:15:01,733
We'll go to the after-party together.

145
00:15:01,733 --> 00:15:03,901
Yes, go ahead.

146
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:09,834
Mini Min Hee, why aren't you coming?

147
00:15:09,834 --> 00:15:11,736
What about Nae Il?

148
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:14,481
Still?

149
00:15:14,481 --> 00:15:16,218
Got it.

150
00:15:25,239 --> 00:15:27,008
Yoo Il Lak!

151
00:15:29,137 --> 00:15:31,556
I heard your performance
today was great.

152
00:15:31,556 --> 00:15:33,339
Sorry I couldn't go.

153
00:15:34,309 --> 00:15:37,070
I heard your performance was better.

154
00:15:37,070 --> 00:15:39,940
That's because Professor von Stresemann conducted.

155
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:44,054
By the way, the losers power was real.

156
00:15:44,054 --> 00:15:46,154
I was surprised this time.

157
00:15:46,154 --> 00:15:48,323
At first, I thought you'd give up.

158
00:15:48,323 --> 00:15:51,626
You guys are great. Really awesome.

159
00:16:05,007 --> 00:16:06,575
See you.

160
00:16:13,553 --> 00:16:15,354
We touched.

161
00:16:20,814 --> 00:16:23,108
The infection on your fingers
is really bad.

162
00:16:23,108 --> 00:16:27,278
- It must be very painful...
- So you're telling me to get surgery?

163
00:16:29,114 --> 00:16:30,793
Doctor...

164
00:16:30,793 --> 00:16:32,617
I'm a cellist.

165
00:16:33,547 --> 00:16:35,078
If I get surgery on my
nerves, there is a chance

166
00:16:35,078 --> 00:16:37,180
that I'll never be able
to play the cello again.

167
00:16:38,305 --> 00:16:40,115
So just write me a prescription.

168
00:16:40,115 --> 00:16:42,776
There's a limit to taking medicine.
It must be even harder to endure...

169
00:16:42,776 --> 00:16:45,178
I will endure it...

170
00:16:47,466 --> 00:16:50,102
I can endure it...

171
00:16:50,970 --> 00:16:52,805
so please write me a prescription.

172
00:16:54,515 --> 00:16:57,585
I still have this
performance I have to do.

173
00:17:47,192 --> 00:17:50,002
I have to tell you something.

174
00:17:50,002 --> 00:17:52,478
Before any more time passes...

175
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:57,786
I loved one girl.

176
00:17:57,786 --> 00:18:00,455
She became my wife

177
00:18:00,455 --> 00:18:04,859
and she still lives as my life partner.

178
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:09,426
That's Composer Grieg's love story.

179
00:18:12,384 --> 00:18:14,442
Yes, Mina.

180
00:18:15,661 --> 00:18:22,368
Yesterday's performance was the one
I should've shown you 20 years ago.

181
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:24,417
Pardon?

182
00:18:24,417 --> 00:18:29,394
I ran away from you back then.

183
00:18:30,652 --> 00:18:33,733
There was a small misunderstanding...

184
00:18:33,733 --> 00:18:37,262
but I only realized it too late
that it was a misunderstanding.

185
00:18:37,262 --> 00:18:40,023
Misunderstanding?
What do you mean by that?

186
00:18:40,023 --> 00:18:47,336
I thought you loved someone else then.

187
00:18:47,336 --> 00:18:49,963
No, how could you think that way...

188
00:18:49,963 --> 00:18:52,966
- I have never...
- Yes, I know, Mina.

189
00:18:53,479 --> 00:18:58,012
When you gave me a chance,
I was happy.

190
00:18:58,012 --> 00:19:00,890
I was so happy to come back.

191
00:19:00,890 --> 00:19:06,974
Now I should say
what I couldn't say before.

192
00:19:09,129 --> 00:19:11,665
Yes, go ahead.

193
00:19:12,528 --> 00:19:14,248
Mina.

194
00:19:14,248 --> 00:19:15,498
Yes.

195
00:19:16,823 --> 00:19:18,684
For me...

196
00:19:28,201 --> 00:19:29,628
Who are you?

197
00:19:29,628 --> 00:19:32,338
Elisse... you found me after all.

198
00:19:32,338 --> 00:19:37,123
Maestro von Stresemann!
Did you have enough fun?

199
00:19:37,123 --> 00:19:39,720
It's time to get back to work.

200
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:42,474
You signed the contract, so
you should follow it!

201
00:19:45,076 --> 00:19:46,812
Let go! Let go!

202
00:19:46,812 --> 00:19:48,372
- Let go!
- Who are you?

203
00:19:48,372 --> 00:19:49,481
What are you doing?

204
00:19:49,481 --> 00:19:54,086
One moment, Elisse.
Give me just one minute.

205
00:19:54,703 --> 00:19:58,422
Get him in the car. We're heading
straight to the airport.

206
00:20:01,675 --> 00:20:04,454
Mina, don't be mistaken.

207
00:20:04,454 --> 00:20:06,756
I'm getting dragged away this time!

208
00:20:08,082 --> 00:20:09,646
Mina! Mina!

209
00:20:09,646 --> 00:20:12,192
Franz! Franz!

210
00:20:12,192 --> 00:20:15,299
- Are you Dean Mina Song?
- Yes.

211
00:20:15,299 --> 00:20:18,658
I'm the manager of the Royal orchestra.

212
00:20:19,845 --> 00:20:21,054
Royal orchestra?

213
00:20:21,054 --> 00:20:25,118
We have a concert, so we have no
choice but to escort Maestro away.

214
00:20:25,118 --> 00:20:26,589
What?

215
00:20:31,607 --> 00:20:35,168
Mina! Mina!

216
00:20:35,168 --> 00:20:36,669
Mina!

217
00:20:48,373 --> 00:20:50,167
He ran away and came here?

218
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:51,716
Professor did that?

219
00:20:52,572 --> 00:20:54,671
A call came into the administrative office

220
00:20:54,671 --> 00:20:57,106
and Professor Do found out about it.

221
00:20:57,964 --> 00:21:00,520
Before the Royal orchestra concert

222
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:03,456
he ran away to Korea because
he wanted to hang out.

223
00:21:06,183 --> 00:21:08,919
That's just like him.

224
00:21:10,270 --> 00:21:13,295
Are you okay?

225
00:21:14,650 --> 00:21:17,860
I just feel bad for you.

226
00:21:17,860 --> 00:21:20,427
I made you take the spotlight as the only

227
00:21:20,427 --> 00:21:22,850
apprentice of Professor von Stresemann...

228
00:21:23,951 --> 00:21:25,608
but now this happened...

229
00:21:25,608 --> 00:21:26,911
It's okay.

230
00:21:26,911 --> 00:21:31,415
I thought it was too quiet
for a world-famous maestro's visit.

231
00:21:32,112 --> 00:21:35,148
I thought it was because he
was shy towards the media.

232
00:21:36,755 --> 00:21:41,559
What about you? It looks like you
became uncomfortable with S Orchestra.

233
00:21:43,637 --> 00:21:46,345
I got the gist from Franz.

234
00:21:46,345 --> 00:21:51,933
You performed with A Orchestra
because of Professor Do.

235
00:21:51,933 --> 00:21:54,648
Franz had a guess, but
just watched it happen.

236
00:21:54,648 --> 00:21:56,182
I'm sorry.

237
00:21:56,910 --> 00:21:58,831
It was my choice.

238
00:21:59,699 --> 00:22:03,948
Yes, if it was your choice, you have
to take the responsibility for it.

239
00:22:03,948 --> 00:22:07,955
Still, thank you for hanging in there.

240
00:22:07,955 --> 00:22:09,332
Yes.

241
00:22:10,789 --> 00:22:12,591
I'll get going now.

242
00:22:24,678 --> 00:22:28,348
Franz von Stresemann...
it's really over with you now.

243
00:22:29,809 --> 00:22:32,211
I will never see you again.

244
00:22:44,624 --> 00:22:48,101
Today we're here to revise
the school regulations.

245
00:22:48,968 --> 00:22:53,832
From this moment
Han Eum will only have one orchestra.

246
00:22:53,832 --> 00:22:57,268
The dean should be here, although
she has no right to vote.

247
00:23:00,219 --> 00:23:03,423
This is the complaint from
Yoon Yi Song Music Festival.

248
00:23:03,423 --> 00:23:08,061
This is the result of Dean Song's
work with the school so far.

249
00:23:19,566 --> 00:23:22,482
Now, we'll vote by show of hands.

250
00:23:22,482 --> 00:23:26,901
Only one orchestra will exist
at Han Eum Academy of Music.

251
00:23:27,699 --> 00:23:29,500
Do you agree?

252
00:23:31,954 --> 00:23:33,560
Professor von Stresemann
got dragged away?

253
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:34,998
Why? By whom?

254
00:23:34,998 --> 00:23:37,458
I heard some really tall
foreigner took him away.

255
00:23:37,458 --> 00:23:39,265
What happens to us now?

256
00:23:39,265 --> 00:23:40,420
What about us?

257
00:23:40,420 --> 00:23:43,982
Professor still protected us.

258
00:23:43,982 --> 00:23:47,551
Yes, because he ran away without
casting his vote, we survived.

259
00:23:47,551 --> 00:23:52,812
Did you forget that he plotted
with A and took away Cha Yoo Jin?

260
00:23:52,812 --> 00:23:54,560
We had a great performance
all by ourselves.

261
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:56,487
It doesn't matter
if we have him or not.

262
00:23:56,487 --> 00:23:59,615
I guess, we did well on our own.

263
00:23:59,615 --> 00:24:01,365
We just need to unite
amongst ourselves like now.

264
00:24:01,365 --> 00:24:03,175
That's right.

265
00:24:03,175 --> 00:24:06,446
By the way, where
did Min Hee and Yoon Hoo go?

266
00:24:06,446 --> 00:24:10,790
I haven't seen Nae Il since
the classical night either.

267
00:24:12,911 --> 00:24:14,445
Sunbae!

268
00:24:16,999 --> 00:24:20,125
- Nae Il disappeared.
- What?

269
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:22,337
Hurry up.

270
00:24:22,337 --> 00:24:24,173
This is coming out of Nae Il's place?

271
00:24:24,173 --> 00:24:25,342
Yes.

272
00:24:31,651 --> 00:24:34,139
You heard the music for two
days, but didn't get any answer?

273
00:24:34,139 --> 00:24:38,591
Yes. At first, I was relieved because
I thought Nae Il was playing it.

274
00:24:38,591 --> 00:24:40,341
But no.

275
00:24:40,341 --> 00:24:44,008
She left with the music on,
but I didn't know that.

276
00:24:44,008 --> 00:24:47,276
Where did she go with the music on?

277
00:24:47,276 --> 00:24:51,347
What do we do, Il Lak?
Nae Il doesn't have anywhere to go.

278
00:24:53,911 --> 00:24:56,981
Nae Il, if you're inside, open the door!

279
00:24:57,579 --> 00:24:58,957
Seol Nae Il!

280
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:02,377
That's shocking.
So you don't know when

281
00:25:02,377 --> 00:25:05,070
Professor von Stresemann
will be coming back?

282
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:08,425
Who knows. Who would know
about his eccentricity?

283
00:25:08,425 --> 00:25:10,928
A lot of things happened,

284
00:25:10,928 --> 00:25:13,030
while you were held up
in your mother's place for three days.

285
00:25:13,540 --> 00:25:15,227
Were you told to inherit
the business again?

286
00:25:15,227 --> 00:25:17,328
It's the same old thing.

287
00:25:19,025 --> 00:25:20,659
You said you had something to say.

288
00:25:22,314 --> 00:25:23,815
What?

289
00:25:25,364 --> 00:25:26,887
Do you want...

290
00:25:28,111 --> 00:25:30,120
to get back together?

291
00:25:31,823 --> 00:25:36,386
I don't like lingering around,
so I thought about just giving up...

292
00:25:36,386 --> 00:25:38,555
but I should tell you.

293
00:25:40,457 --> 00:25:43,919
I think I still have feelings for you.

294
00:25:43,919 --> 00:25:46,647
- Do Kyung...
- I just had that thought.

295
00:25:46,647 --> 00:25:48,088
It would be nice to quit singing

296
00:25:48,088 --> 00:25:52,970
and support you in
becoming a conductor.

297
00:25:56,369 --> 00:25:58,271
You don't want to?

298
00:26:01,019 --> 00:26:02,519
You don't want that.

299
00:26:05,274 --> 00:26:10,488
Still, will you consider
about the matter deeply?

300
00:26:10,488 --> 00:26:12,225
It's not that I don't want to.

301
00:26:12,225 --> 00:26:15,409
I was just surprised because
I've never thought about it.

302
00:26:15,409 --> 00:26:20,313
Then will you think about it seriously?

303
00:26:21,832 --> 00:26:24,301
- Yoo Jin Sunbae!
- Almighty Cha!

304
00:26:25,544 --> 00:26:27,012
What?

305
00:26:29,840 --> 00:26:32,216
Did something happen to the orchestra?

306
00:26:32,216 --> 00:26:34,386
Have you seen Seol Nae Il?

307
00:26:34,386 --> 00:26:35,979
Seol Nae Il?

308
00:26:36,595 --> 00:26:38,644
I haven't seen her
since the performance.

309
00:26:38,644 --> 00:26:40,224
We can't reach her.

310
00:26:40,224 --> 00:26:43,583
We heard piano music from the
house, so we thought she was home.

311
00:26:43,583 --> 00:26:45,522
But it looks like she
left with the music on.

312
00:26:45,522 --> 00:26:47,008
She didn't even come to classes.

313
00:26:47,008 --> 00:26:51,373
She saw you... and Chae Do Kyung
together at the classical night

314
00:26:51,373 --> 00:26:53,405
and she was really shocked.

315
00:26:53,405 --> 00:26:56,517
Because of Do Kyung and me? Why?

316
00:26:57,241 --> 00:27:00,132
Anyway you should hurry.
She disappeared.

317
00:27:00,132 --> 00:27:04,219
Okay. I'll go to her house.
You should look for her in other places.

318
00:27:05,398 --> 00:27:07,022
Wait for me, Yoo Jin.

319
00:27:07,022 --> 00:27:09,991
- Let's spread out and look for her.
- Okay.

320
00:27:13,091 --> 00:27:14,594
Seol Nae Il!

321
00:27:17,513 --> 00:27:19,674
You know the code?

322
00:27:19,674 --> 00:27:21,442
It's the same as mine.

323
00:27:29,399 --> 00:27:30,733
Seol Nae Il!

324
00:27:32,165 --> 00:27:34,701
Wake up! Wake up!

325
00:27:40,285 --> 00:27:42,620
What happened? Can you see me?

326
00:27:54,007 --> 00:27:56,009
Wait a minute...

327
00:27:56,509 --> 00:27:58,478
Have you been playing
the piano for days?

328
00:27:59,582 --> 00:28:01,972
- It hurts...
- How much did you play?

329
00:28:01,972 --> 00:28:05,100
Stop, Yoo Jin. She needs a hot pad.

330
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:07,400
Will you bring me a warm towel?

331
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:09,568
Okay, I'll be right back.

332
00:28:28,417 --> 00:28:30,791
You saw Yoo Jin and me.

333
00:28:32,658 --> 00:28:34,159
I'm sorry.

334
00:28:35,841 --> 00:28:38,778
But we were going to get
back together again.

335
00:28:39,380 --> 00:28:41,732
Yoo Jin and I...

336
00:28:41,732 --> 00:28:46,706
are the same kind
with similar thoughts and directions.

337
00:28:46,706 --> 00:28:51,044
You also know who suits Yoo Jin better.

338
00:28:51,544 --> 00:28:56,981
So... you should get over him soon.

339
00:29:03,118 --> 00:29:05,120
Which side is hurting?

340
00:29:17,174 --> 00:29:22,144
I can't get you out of my head...

341
00:29:23,680 --> 00:29:25,182
What?

342
00:29:26,232 --> 00:29:29,782
Your Grieg piano concerto...

343
00:29:29,782 --> 00:29:33,353
keeps circling in my head.

344
00:29:34,192 --> 00:29:35,780
Here!

345
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:39,359
It's not leaving my head.

346
00:29:41,782 --> 00:29:43,363
I...

347
00:29:44,253 --> 00:29:47,444
want to play Grieg's
piano concerto like you.

348
00:29:49,602 --> 00:29:51,121
Intense...

349
00:29:52,394 --> 00:29:54,966
vivid and splendid.

350
00:29:57,881 --> 00:30:01,382
I've never played that way.

351
00:30:01,382 --> 00:30:03,595
How are you going to play the
piano with these arms, idiot!

352
00:30:03,595 --> 00:30:05,864
I couldn't do anything else.

353
00:30:06,352 --> 00:30:09,380
I couldn't get away from
your piano performance.

354
00:30:10,519 --> 00:30:15,791
I also want to play the piano in
a way that possesses people!

355
00:30:21,254 --> 00:30:22,869
Sunbae...

356
00:30:25,325 --> 00:30:27,051
Okay.

357
00:30:27,051 --> 00:30:30,664
Okay, just put the hot towel on.

358
00:30:30,664 --> 00:30:34,368
When your shoulders feel
better, let's play then.

359
00:30:35,415 --> 00:30:38,672
Really? Really?

360
00:30:38,672 --> 00:30:40,541
Yes, really.

361
00:30:41,300 --> 00:30:42,601
Really.

362
00:30:52,811 --> 00:30:54,738
Let's go now, Yoo Jin.

363
00:30:54,738 --> 00:30:56,730
She seems to be doing fine.

364
00:30:59,610 --> 00:31:01,178
Yoo Jin...

365
00:31:02,028 --> 00:31:04,488
This is insane, Seol Nae Il.

366
00:31:04,488 --> 00:31:07,239
I didn't know you'd get me excited.

367
00:31:07,239 --> 00:31:09,028
What?

368
00:31:09,028 --> 00:31:12,172
Have you heard of such
genuine compliment?

369
00:31:12,172 --> 00:31:13,973
From Seol Nae Il.

370
00:31:14,661 --> 00:31:17,109
She memorizes everything by hearing.

371
00:31:17,109 --> 00:31:19,148
That extraordinary girl.

372
00:31:23,217 --> 00:31:27,555
She was possessed by
my piano performance.

373
00:31:28,347 --> 00:31:30,040
Yoo Jin...

374
00:33:10,199 --> 00:33:12,413
The one who's playing the piano...

375
00:33:13,192 --> 00:33:15,954
Is it really Seol Nae Il,
not Cha Yoo Jin?

376
00:33:15,954 --> 00:33:18,210
It's strange.

377
00:33:18,210 --> 00:33:22,250
It sounds like the Grieg piano concerto
that Yoo Jin played before.

378
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:24,463
What the heck, Seol Nae Il?

379
00:33:24,463 --> 00:33:27,096
You're really... awesome.

380
00:33:30,302 --> 00:33:34,460
She's... really Nae Il, right?

381
00:33:41,438 --> 00:33:44,174
Hi, Mom.

382
00:33:46,151 --> 00:33:49,108
When I was in Italy as a kid...

383
00:33:49,108 --> 00:33:52,002
Do you know what the
toughest thing was for me?

384
00:33:53,158 --> 00:33:55,919
The kids were playing games only

385
00:33:55,919 --> 00:33:58,488
they knew using the words
I don't even understand

386
00:34:00,866 --> 00:34:03,456
No matter how much I
wanted to jump in...

387
00:34:03,456 --> 00:34:07,882
I couldn't understand
a thing with my brain.

388
00:35:06,857 --> 00:35:09,492
What's your dream, Baby?

389
00:35:11,612 --> 00:35:14,047
A happy pianist?

390
00:35:14,827 --> 00:35:16,175
What?

391
00:35:17,407 --> 00:35:21,288
No, my dream is to become
a kindergarten teacher.

392
00:35:21,288 --> 00:35:23,410
A kindergarten teacher?

393
00:35:24,196 --> 00:35:25,557
And also...

394
00:35:25,557 --> 00:35:29,394
I want to become Yoo Jin's wife.

395
00:35:30,530 --> 00:35:33,097
I ended up telling you.

396
00:35:33,097 --> 00:35:34,658
Baby...

397
00:35:35,969 --> 00:35:39,806
You have to watch
Cha Yoo Jin's performance this time.

398
00:35:40,986 --> 00:35:43,224
It will be the best performance.

399
00:35:43,224 --> 00:35:45,691
His performances are always great.

400
00:35:45,691 --> 00:35:48,132
He's the best in our school.

401
00:35:48,132 --> 00:35:50,955
Cha Yoo Jin will become
above and beyond that.

402
00:35:51,443 --> 00:35:54,045
He will fly far away.

403
00:35:54,706 --> 00:35:58,343
To a place where your eyes
and hands can't touch.

404
00:35:59,477 --> 00:36:01,638
If things remain as it is now,

405
00:36:01,638 --> 00:36:05,074
you can't be with Yoo Jin, Baby.

406
00:36:06,083 --> 00:36:07,550
Baby...

407
00:36:08,043 --> 00:36:10,512
if you want to be with Yoo Jin...

408
00:36:10,512 --> 00:36:14,506
you have confront music face-to-face.

409
00:36:58,010 --> 00:37:00,212
Don't forget.

410
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:08,120
Time and Cha Yoo Jin
won't wait for you.

411
00:37:18,113 --> 00:37:20,815
- Nae Il
- Seol Nae Il!!

412
00:37:23,827 --> 00:37:26,411
- Are you okay?
- Me?

413
00:37:26,411 --> 00:37:28,538
If you turn your phone off
and disappear again...

414
00:37:28,538 --> 00:37:30,039
I'm going to kill you.

415
00:37:30,039 --> 00:37:33,212
She was just playing the piano.
You're okay, right?

416
00:37:33,212 --> 00:37:36,906
Nae Il, you looked like Son Soo Ji.

417
00:37:36,906 --> 00:37:39,108
You were really great.

418
00:37:40,719 --> 00:37:44,410
Why are you all like this?

419
00:37:44,410 --> 00:37:46,912
We were all worried about you.

420
00:37:47,515 --> 00:37:52,217
Should I treat you all to lunch to
celebrate Seol Nae Il's safe return?

421
00:37:52,217 --> 00:37:54,334
- Lunch?
- Lunch?

422
00:37:56,652 --> 00:38:00,349
- Soft bread is better, right?
- No, multi-grain bread.

423
00:38:00,349 --> 00:38:04,451
Since it's on Yoon Hoo, we
should go for quality, not quantity.

424
00:38:04,451 --> 00:38:08,755
Leave out the vegetables.
Meat, only meat.

425
00:38:11,206 --> 00:38:13,472
You're taking over 10 minutes
to make your decision?

426
00:38:13,472 --> 00:38:16,174
We're almost done!

427
00:38:27,099 --> 00:38:29,034
I'm not going to steal yours!

428
00:38:30,769 --> 00:38:33,522
Take your time. We're full.

429
00:38:33,522 --> 00:38:35,698
Thank you.

430
00:38:42,698 --> 00:38:45,284
Cellists' hands look similar.

431
00:38:45,284 --> 00:38:47,486
Why? Yoon Hoo's hands look
similar to someone else's?

432
00:38:47,486 --> 00:38:52,257
Yes, to the one who saved
Yoo Jin at the water park.

433
00:38:52,257 --> 00:38:55,041
He had the hands of a cellist.

434
00:38:55,041 --> 00:38:59,145
His left hand was bigger,
and knuckles were bent.

435
00:38:59,145 --> 00:39:02,020
You know the hands
that practiced a lot.

436
00:39:02,020 --> 00:39:03,452
Just like...

437
00:39:04,020 --> 00:39:06,302
Yoon Hoo's hands?

438
00:39:06,302 --> 00:39:07,338
What?

439
00:39:07,338 --> 00:39:11,275
Yes, hands just like this
saved Yoo Jin Sunbae.

440
00:39:12,884 --> 00:39:14,813
I didn't get to say thank you then.

441
00:39:14,813 --> 00:39:17,516
If I saw his face, I'd have looked for him.

442
00:39:18,991 --> 00:39:20,483
So you didn't see the face.

443
00:39:20,483 --> 00:39:22,487
Why do you keep talking about Yoo Jin?

444
00:39:22,487 --> 00:39:24,904
He wasn't even curious about
who saved him!

445
00:39:24,904 --> 00:39:27,994
That's because Yoo Jin doesn't
know who saved him...

446
00:39:29,203 --> 00:39:30,804
I'm leaving first.

447
00:39:31,494 --> 00:39:35,132
I'm sorry, Lak. I won't
bring it up anymore.

448
00:39:38,683 --> 00:39:41,548
The delicious sandwich that
Yoon Hoo bought for me.

449
00:39:41,548 --> 00:39:44,484
I fed you all along and you
follow him just for this?

450
00:39:45,290 --> 00:39:47,760
Why did she post the picture here?

451
00:39:50,402 --> 00:39:52,295
To show me?

452
00:39:52,295 --> 00:39:54,332
Of course I wouldn't
look at this stuff.

453
00:39:54,332 --> 00:39:56,835
I don't get agitated
by things like this.

454
00:39:57,773 --> 00:39:59,508
What is she thinking...

455
00:40:02,319 --> 00:40:04,454
Did something bad happen?

456
00:40:06,823 --> 00:40:08,316
Sorry about yesterday.

457
00:40:08,316 --> 00:40:10,008
I didn't see you leave.

458
00:40:10,008 --> 00:40:14,226
It's okay. I know you weren't
in the situation to worry about me.

459
00:40:16,542 --> 00:40:19,169
I thought about it...
Between you and me...

460
00:40:19,169 --> 00:40:20,941
I...

461
00:40:20,941 --> 00:40:22,572
plan to go study abroad.

462
00:40:23,315 --> 00:40:25,467
Study abroad? Why, so suddenly?

463
00:40:25,467 --> 00:40:30,829
When I went for the audition last time,
I confirmed my level in a brutal way.

464
00:40:30,829 --> 00:40:33,932
So I even thought about
quitting singing...

465
00:40:34,587 --> 00:40:36,221
but I want to try again.

466
00:40:37,129 --> 00:40:40,732
Even if I don't get the first place,
I'll try to get the second place.

467
00:40:42,109 --> 00:40:43,577
Do Kyung...

468
00:40:44,359 --> 00:40:47,503
- I like your voice.
- I know.

469
00:40:47,503 --> 00:40:49,740
That's why you liked me.

470
00:40:51,451 --> 00:40:52,754
Then...

471
00:40:52,754 --> 00:40:55,058
why do you like Seol Nae Il?

472
00:40:56,087 --> 00:40:57,680
Why would I like Seol Nae Il?

473
00:40:57,680 --> 00:40:59,082
No?

474
00:40:59,945 --> 00:41:02,648
Sorry. It just looked different.

475
00:41:03,695 --> 00:41:06,464
Well, she's more like
a younger sister to you,

476
00:41:07,412 --> 00:41:11,082
she can't be a girlfriend
to Cha Yoo Jin, can she?

477
00:41:17,195 --> 00:41:19,497
I'll call you when I get settled.

478
00:41:24,829 --> 00:41:27,123
Say hello to your mother.

479
00:41:27,123 --> 00:41:28,624
Okay.

480
00:41:48,986 --> 00:41:51,714
It's not to show off technical glamor.

481
00:41:51,714 --> 00:41:54,949
Performances realize the theme
using different instruments.

482
00:41:54,949 --> 00:41:57,042
In a way that they push
and pull each other's

483
00:41:57,042 --> 00:41:59,170
sound to run towards the theme.

484
00:41:59,170 --> 00:42:01,806
It's similar to playing hard
to get between couples.

485
00:42:02,358 --> 00:42:05,861
A concerto for two violins
in D minor by Bach.

486
00:42:05,861 --> 00:42:08,322
The most important thing is balance.

487
00:42:08,322 --> 00:42:10,282
That's what you're learning.

488
00:42:10,282 --> 00:42:13,618
Find a partner on your own and
practice until next week.

489
00:42:14,119 --> 00:42:16,421
Thank you!

490
00:42:18,038 --> 00:42:21,792
Shi Won, let's do it together. If I fail
this time, my parents will kill me!

491
00:42:21,792 --> 00:42:24,220
He won't be any help to you,
so do it with me.

492
00:42:24,220 --> 00:42:26,004
Why is he holding her shoulder?

493
00:42:26,004 --> 00:42:28,593
- I haven't done that to her yet...
- I'm much better in balancing than you guys!

494
00:42:28,593 --> 00:42:32,052
Sorry, sorry. But I have someone
else I want to play with.

495
00:42:32,052 --> 00:42:33,843
Who?

496
00:42:33,843 --> 00:42:35,305
Yoo Il Lak.

497
00:42:35,860 --> 00:42:37,161
What?

498
00:42:40,269 --> 00:42:41,854
Do you want to play together?

499
00:42:41,854 --> 00:42:44,256
Like the time we had a battle?

500
00:42:50,782 --> 00:42:52,842
Father! Father! Father!

501
00:42:52,842 --> 00:42:55,242
What? My son, my son! What?

502
00:42:55,242 --> 00:42:57,619
- I have a big problem.
- What? Did you have a fight?

503
00:42:57,619 --> 00:42:59,538
No, I didn't have a fight...

504
00:42:59,538 --> 00:43:02,567
I don't know how to say this.
I've never had this happen before...

505
00:43:02,567 --> 00:43:05,661
Father, why is the world so beautiful?

506
00:43:05,661 --> 00:43:07,462
Why is the sky so blue

507
00:43:07,462 --> 00:43:10,497
and why are the clouds
like cotton candy?

508
00:43:13,766 --> 00:43:16,638
Father, thank you for
bringing me into this world.

509
00:43:16,638 --> 00:43:19,207
I'll have a really great life now.

510
00:43:22,644 --> 00:43:27,481
That's exactly what I did before
I went out with his mother.

511
00:43:31,320 --> 00:43:32,755
Chae Do Kyung.

512
00:43:35,115 --> 00:43:36,995
I heard you're preparing
to go study abroad?

513
00:43:36,995 --> 00:43:38,741
Yes.

514
00:43:38,741 --> 00:43:40,532
I'm disappointed.

515
00:43:40,532 --> 00:43:43,081
I thought things were going
well with that rude one.

516
00:43:43,081 --> 00:43:46,585
I think Yoo Jin will go
out with Seol Nae Il.

517
00:43:47,419 --> 00:43:51,006
He loves music more than women.

518
00:43:51,006 --> 00:43:53,133
Why would you bring up
Seol Nae Il here?

519
00:43:53,133 --> 00:43:55,834
Those two seem to be
in the same category.

520
00:43:55,834 --> 00:43:58,368
Seol Nae Il is in the same
category as Cha Yoo Jin?

521
00:43:58,368 --> 00:44:00,503
The one who plays the fart song?

522
00:44:01,517 --> 00:44:03,869
That's right.

523
00:44:03,869 --> 00:44:10,309
Baby is the pianist that you
were looking for, Professor Do.

524
00:44:17,221 --> 00:44:18,802
Ma'am!

525
00:44:20,452 --> 00:44:22,037
What's going on?

526
00:44:22,037 --> 00:44:23,550
Professor Do, you're being rude.

527
00:44:23,550 --> 00:44:26,419
You were the one who admitted
Seol Nae Il as a special case.

528
00:44:27,813 --> 00:44:31,149
Did you know that she was extraordinary?

529
00:44:32,673 --> 00:44:35,867
I assumed that she's special.

530
00:44:35,867 --> 00:44:38,628
Then why do you leave her
play the fart song?

531
00:44:38,628 --> 00:44:42,657
It's my principle to
leave her alone to enjoy

532
00:44:42,657 --> 00:44:44,184
and wait until she wants
to make an effort.

533
00:44:44,184 --> 00:44:47,727
That's not education, that's neglect!

534
00:44:47,727 --> 00:44:51,470
I didn't like anything you've
done so far, but I held back.

535
00:44:51,470 --> 00:44:54,301
Because I respected how you cared
for the school and the students.

536
00:44:54,301 --> 00:44:59,407
But you know how desperately we're
looking for a piano genius.

537
00:44:59,407 --> 00:45:01,535
Forcing someone to do
something they don't like is violence.

538
00:45:01,535 --> 00:45:04,096
A genius is also made with
timing and education.

539
00:45:04,096 --> 00:45:06,131
You have to teach her even
if she doesn't want to!

540
00:45:08,125 --> 00:45:10,527
That's what's best for the student.

541
00:45:13,564 --> 00:45:16,500
Did you know the board of directors
revised school regulations?

542
00:45:20,539 --> 00:45:22,005
What did you say?

543
00:45:22,005 --> 00:45:25,123
I'm sure no one told you.

544
00:45:25,123 --> 00:45:28,604
It's a very logical rule that would

545
00:45:28,604 --> 00:45:30,573
recognize only one
orchestra in the school.

546
00:45:32,816 --> 00:45:35,524
Now it's your turn to
make the announcement.

547
00:45:35,524 --> 00:45:39,865
About S Orchestra's official dissolution.

548
00:45:50,295 --> 00:45:52,044
Why are we getting dissolved?

549
00:45:52,044 --> 00:45:53,420
You're mistaken.

550
00:45:53,420 --> 00:45:55,756
'One school, one orchestra'
is the rule.

551
00:45:55,756 --> 00:45:57,458
Would they dissolve A?

552
00:45:58,297 --> 00:46:03,902
Then the board of directors,
alumni, and sponsors will rise up.

553
00:46:03,902 --> 00:46:07,063
But we did well in our performance.

554
00:46:07,063 --> 00:46:08,977
Come with us before it's too late.

555
00:46:08,977 --> 00:46:11,188
You can't practice the
timpani by yourself.

556
00:46:11,188 --> 00:46:13,524
Cha Yoo Jin probably knew that
S was going to get dissolved.

557
00:46:13,524 --> 00:46:16,424
I'm sure that's why he performed
with us at the classical night.

558
00:46:17,190 --> 00:46:19,457
He jumped from the sinking ship

559
00:46:19,457 --> 00:46:21,365
and climbed quickly to our ship.

560
00:46:21,365 --> 00:46:23,242
- What?
- Well...

561
00:46:23,242 --> 00:46:25,410
It looks he's on Professor
Do Kang Jae's line these days.

562
00:46:25,410 --> 00:46:27,623
Why is ours getting dissolved?

563
00:46:28,220 --> 00:46:30,015
Il Lak...

564
00:46:30,015 --> 00:46:34,286
Are you saying that Cha Yoo Jin
knew about our dissolution?

565
00:46:41,093 --> 00:46:43,061
The dissolution of S Orchestra?

566
00:46:43,654 --> 00:46:45,984
The Professor didn't even vote.

567
00:46:46,825 --> 00:46:51,162
They let his odd behavior go
because it was von Stresemann.

568
00:46:51,782 --> 00:46:55,519
That immature act wouldn't work anymore.

569
00:46:56,561 --> 00:47:02,280
Franz knew that he couldn't stop
the dissolution of S Orchestra.

570
00:47:03,115 --> 00:47:07,248
He only bought some time.

571
00:47:10,497 --> 00:47:12,041
Is there...

572
00:47:13,282 --> 00:47:15,541
really no way?

573
00:47:15,541 --> 00:47:18,083
They really have nowhere else to go.

574
00:47:18,083 --> 00:47:19,618
Those kids...

575
00:47:22,634 --> 00:47:24,686
They're my friends.

576
00:47:24,686 --> 00:47:29,196
Dissolution of S Orchestra is inevitable.

577
00:47:30,350 --> 00:47:32,651
Is there really no way?

578
00:47:32,651 --> 00:47:35,387
There is one...

579
00:47:36,857 --> 00:47:38,734
Yoo Jin...

580
00:47:38,734 --> 00:47:42,489
the burden you have to carry
is too big.

581
00:47:48,680 --> 00:47:50,807
It's not confirmed yet.

582
00:47:50,807 --> 00:47:53,334
I'm sure Almighty Cha
didn't know either.

583
00:47:53,334 --> 00:47:56,129
- Right, Mini Min Hee?
- I'm not sure.

584
00:47:56,129 --> 00:47:59,598
Whether Cha Yoo Jin knew about it or
not, it's true that he abandoned us.

585
00:48:08,666 --> 00:48:10,335
Are you worried about something?

586
00:48:11,308 --> 00:48:12,873
Sunbae...

587
00:48:17,898 --> 00:48:19,513
Well...

588
00:48:21,568 --> 00:48:25,138
Yoo Jin Sunbae doesn't let
me come to his house.

589
00:48:25,824 --> 00:48:28,826
There's no point living next doors...

590
00:48:30,134 --> 00:48:32,235
So you were neighbors.

591
00:48:33,905 --> 00:48:37,282
What do you like about Cha Yoo Jin?

592
00:48:37,282 --> 00:48:39,517
His looks? His talent?

593
00:48:43,423 --> 00:48:45,926
I liked his good looks...

594
00:48:45,926 --> 00:48:50,297
I liked that he was good at
conducting and playing the piano...

595
00:48:51,226 --> 00:48:57,348
but these days I wish he was ugly and
wasn't good at playing the piano.

596
00:48:59,481 --> 00:49:01,583
Am I strange?

597
00:49:04,653 --> 00:49:08,849
What does Cha Yoo Jin
mean to Seol Nae Il?

598
00:49:08,849 --> 00:49:10,985
He's just Cha Yoo Jin Sunbae.

599
00:49:11,621 --> 00:49:15,998
The only one in the world.

600
00:49:15,998 --> 00:49:21,636
Then... what would Seol Nae Il
mean to Cha Yoo Jin?

601
00:49:23,380 --> 00:49:26,150
I'm... not sure.

602
00:49:30,888 --> 00:49:32,723
You should ask him yourself.

603
00:49:37,815 --> 00:49:41,118
- Should I ask him for you?
- No, don't do it.

604
00:49:41,773 --> 00:49:43,241
Ask what?

605
00:49:46,445 --> 00:49:49,348
Nae Il says it's a secret.

606
00:49:49,921 --> 00:49:51,556
What's a secret?

607
00:49:52,176 --> 00:49:53,434
Aren't you going to tell me?

608
00:49:53,434 --> 00:49:55,929
I'm not going to tell you. I won't.

609
00:49:55,929 --> 00:49:58,798
Can't you do something about that
intimidating tone of speech?

610
00:49:59,436 --> 00:50:01,371
Is it nature or a habit?

611
00:50:02,240 --> 00:50:03,541
What?

612
00:50:04,671 --> 00:50:06,718
If you were born with it, then fix it.

613
00:50:06,718 --> 00:50:07,841
If it's a habit, then change it.

614
00:50:07,841 --> 00:50:10,343
You should fix that habit of lecturing.

615
00:50:11,303 --> 00:50:12,730
Let's go.

616
00:50:24,441 --> 00:50:27,006
Mind your manners towards a woman.

617
00:50:38,330 --> 00:50:40,040
What a show...

618
00:50:40,040 --> 00:50:40,916
Let's go.

619
00:50:40,916 --> 00:50:43,461
Are you okay, Yoon Hoo?

620
00:50:43,461 --> 00:50:45,178
Does it hurt a lot?

621
00:50:47,422 --> 00:50:49,249
Yoon Hoo! Yoon Hoo!

622
00:50:49,249 --> 00:50:50,884
Are you okay?

623
00:50:50,884 --> 00:50:53,031
Yoon Hoo, are you okay?

624
00:50:53,031 --> 00:50:55,533
- What happened?
- His hand seems to be hurting.

625
00:50:57,260 --> 00:50:59,560
- What did you do to him?
- I just shook off his hand.

626
00:50:59,560 --> 00:51:01,795
You just shook it off and
Yoon Hoo feels this pain?

627
00:51:04,542 --> 00:51:06,010
It's true.

628
00:51:06,010 --> 00:51:07,946
How can I trust you?

629
00:51:07,946 --> 00:51:10,028
You knew about the dissolution
but you still left.

630
00:51:10,028 --> 00:51:13,081
Lak, what are you doing?
Yoo Jin didn't do anything wrong.

631
00:51:13,081 --> 00:51:16,326
- It's not Cha Yoo Jin.
- Don't you need to go see a doctor?

632
00:51:16,326 --> 00:51:18,838
Cellist shouldn't get his hands hurt.

633
00:51:33,677 --> 00:51:38,153
Since when were you all
friends with the Juilliard?

634
00:51:38,153 --> 00:51:40,957
Not even believing me!

635
00:51:40,957 --> 00:51:42,592
Taking his side!

636
00:51:43,080 --> 00:51:44,195
Yoo Il Lak!

637
00:51:44,195 --> 00:51:46,157
Ma Su Min! Choi Min Hee!

638
00:51:46,157 --> 00:51:47,876
Seol Nae Il!

639
00:52:23,143 --> 00:52:25,034
My stuff...

640
00:52:28,500 --> 00:52:30,201
Sunbae!

641
00:52:34,932 --> 00:52:37,256
He even changed the code.

642
00:52:38,603 --> 00:52:39,701
Sunbae!

643
00:52:39,701 --> 00:52:41,695
I got rid of all your stuff.

644
00:52:41,695 --> 00:52:44,248
Don't think about coming here now.

645
00:52:44,248 --> 00:52:46,583
Wait! Wait!

646
00:52:46,583 --> 00:52:48,777
I still have a lot left.

647
00:52:48,777 --> 00:52:51,313
I won't leave until you give
them all back to me!

648
00:52:57,970 --> 00:53:00,038
Peter Pan?

649
00:53:13,378 --> 00:53:15,613
You hid this here?

650
00:53:24,888 --> 00:53:26,206
Found it.

651
00:53:26,206 --> 00:53:27,416
Found it!

652
00:53:27,416 --> 00:53:29,651
Wait, there is one more.

653
00:53:35,382 --> 00:53:37,583
When did you get
all the way here?

654
00:53:46,518 --> 00:53:48,020
Why are there so much?

655
00:53:48,020 --> 00:53:50,483
There are traces of
Seol Nae Il everywhere!

656
00:54:00,616 --> 00:54:02,647
It's all clean.

657
00:54:02,647 --> 00:54:07,084
There is no trace of Seol Nae Il
at my place now.

658
00:54:15,214 --> 00:54:17,156
There is more.

659
00:54:18,043 --> 00:54:23,201
Sunbae, you'll be tired,
can I come in and find them myself?

660
00:54:23,201 --> 00:54:26,650
I'll clean up everything and leave.
I mean it.

661
00:54:26,650 --> 00:54:29,561
I'm really going to just
get my stuff and leave.

662
00:54:29,561 --> 00:54:31,555
Still, I can't come in?

663
00:54:31,555 --> 00:54:33,390
Please?

664
00:54:41,907 --> 00:54:43,667
Sunbae...

665
00:54:44,994 --> 00:54:49,140
did I do something really wrong?

666
00:54:50,435 --> 00:54:52,068
If not...

667
00:54:53,707 --> 00:54:56,604
do you really
hate me that much?

668
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:11,877
It's not because of you.

669
00:55:12,688 --> 00:55:14,154
It's me.

670
00:55:39,684 --> 00:55:44,021
Professor Ahn Geon Sung,
I'm sorry.

671
00:55:44,021 --> 00:55:47,291
I missed a lot of lessons...

672
00:55:48,472 --> 00:55:52,376
I'm asking for another fun lesson today.

673
00:55:58,814 --> 00:56:02,073
Hello, Professor.

674
00:56:02,073 --> 00:56:05,282
But I think you found
the wrong lesson room.

675
00:56:05,282 --> 00:56:06,950
No, not at all.

676
00:56:06,950 --> 00:56:10,015
I believe you haven't received
a proper notice from Professor Ahn.

677
00:56:10,015 --> 00:56:14,663
I'm in charge of your special
lessons starting today.

678
00:56:14,663 --> 00:56:17,586
We don't need to introduce
ourselves, do we?

679
00:56:22,333 --> 00:56:26,803
Nae Il, are you taking
lessons from Professor Do?

680
00:56:30,707 --> 00:56:35,270
No, my teacher is
Professor Ahn Geon Sung.

681
00:56:35,270 --> 00:56:39,341
Right? He must be mistaken.

682
00:56:46,490 --> 00:56:48,417
Stop playing around!

683
00:56:48,417 --> 00:56:51,614
If you are a pianist,
get serious in front of the piano!

684
00:56:51,614 --> 00:56:56,319
Because of this nonsense,
I didn't recognize your talent.

685
00:57:02,339 --> 00:57:05,029
I'm sure you know very well about me.

686
00:57:05,029 --> 00:57:09,704
All the award winners from
Han Eum went through me.

687
00:57:16,941 --> 00:57:19,565
I want to train you to be the best.

688
00:57:19,565 --> 00:57:22,150
With your ability, like last time
when you played Eroica,

689
00:57:22,150 --> 00:57:23,652
it's not that difficult.

690
00:57:23,652 --> 00:57:25,891
You haven't met the right teacher,

691
00:57:25,891 --> 00:57:28,278
so you probably don't know your talent...

692
00:57:28,278 --> 00:57:32,216
Seol Nae Il,
you're an amazing gemstone.

693
00:57:32,783 --> 00:57:34,951
Depending on who works on you,

694
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:38,208
you could become
a stone or a diamond.

695
00:57:40,502 --> 00:57:42,213
I will make you

696
00:57:42,213 --> 00:57:46,592
the best pianist ever,
even better than Son Soo Ji.

697
00:57:54,224 --> 00:57:58,256
Imagine Seol Nae Il,
the world-famous pianist.

698
00:57:58,256 --> 00:58:02,688
I will become the teacher
who trained a world-famous pianist.

699
00:58:02,688 --> 00:58:04,695
I don't want to be a
world-famous pianist!

700
00:58:04,695 --> 00:58:06,697
I'm not going to
practice anymore!

701
00:58:07,404 --> 00:58:08,939
Practice!

702
00:58:34,379 --> 00:58:36,982
I don't want to become a pianist.

703
00:58:38,376 --> 00:58:40,502
I'm not going to practice.

704
00:58:42,981 --> 00:58:45,316
Seol Nae Il! l Seol Nae Il!

705
00:58:46,137 --> 00:58:48,305
Seol Nae Il! l Don't go!

706
00:59:22,563 --> 00:59:24,215
Just for a while...

707
00:59:24,761 --> 00:59:26,366
That's all I need.

708
00:59:28,110 --> 00:59:30,512
I'll just hold it for a minute.

709
00:59:36,193 --> 00:59:39,288
As always, your hands comfort me.

710
00:59:39,288 --> 00:59:40,889
What happened?

711
00:59:41,620 --> 00:59:43,169
Sunbae...

712
00:59:43,801 --> 00:59:45,612
It's strange.

713
00:59:46,083 --> 00:59:51,592
Professor Do Kang Jae came in for
my lesson instead of Professor Ahn.

714
00:59:51,592 --> 00:59:54,161
I'm Professor Ahn's student.

715
00:59:54,792 --> 00:59:58,348
Professor Do doesn't have
a good personality

716
00:59:58,348 --> 01:00:00,316
But he's the best
in the piano major.

717
01:00:00,851 --> 01:00:02,978
Don't you know
it's a good opportunity for you?

718
01:00:02,978 --> 01:00:05,648
I know Professor Ahn is nice...

719
01:00:05,648 --> 01:00:08,926
but you need a strict teacher.

720
01:00:08,926 --> 01:00:11,515
I don't need a strict teacher.

721
01:00:11,515 --> 01:00:15,219
You do. That's how you can improve.

722
01:00:18,660 --> 01:00:20,871
He asked me about your talent...

723
01:00:20,871 --> 01:00:24,141
So I told him that you'd change
when you meet a good leader.

724
01:00:24,955 --> 01:00:27,419
But having a first lesson already...

725
01:00:27,419 --> 01:00:30,458
Professor Do sure is fast.

726
01:00:43,723 --> 01:00:45,640
Yes, Professor.

727
01:00:45,640 --> 01:00:48,091
Seol Nae Il is with me.

728
01:00:48,732 --> 01:00:50,067
I'll bring her.

729
01:00:53,362 --> 01:00:55,572
Let's go. He's still waiting for you.

730
01:00:55,572 --> 01:00:57,007
Let's get to your lesson...

731
01:01:01,732 --> 01:01:03,156
Seol Nae Il.

732
01:01:03,927 --> 01:01:05,713
I don't want to.

733
01:01:07,037 --> 01:01:12,375
I don't need any good opportunities.

734
01:01:12,840 --> 01:01:19,280
Crying, getting hit, getting hurt,
being in pain and everyday...

735
01:01:22,224 --> 01:01:24,787
'That's how you become
a successful pianist!'

736
01:01:24,787 --> 01:01:27,051
You must do that!

737
01:01:28,063 --> 01:01:31,709
I really don't need any of that.

738
01:01:31,709 --> 01:01:34,078
So why do you keep forcing me?

739
01:01:34,759 --> 01:01:37,761
I said I don't want harsh lessons,
so why do you keep on insisting?

740
01:01:41,743 --> 01:01:45,288
You're just the same.

741
01:01:46,864 --> 01:01:49,933
You're just the same as those people.
